                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d572">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94112/55: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-10T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 10, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 10—1:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>590. My 588, September 9, 10 p.m. Cadogan has just informed me that the
                    instructions to Tokyo were sent without change this afternoon. They had been
                    delayed because the Foreign Secretary had found when he reached Paris yesterday
                    afternoon that the French were proceeding along a somewhat different line. After
                    communicating with London the Foreign Secretary authorized the despatch of the
                    British instructions as they stood.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
